    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan></name> <name><expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avius</ex></expan></name> <name>Optatus</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/>pro salute
                    <lb n="3"/>sua et <expan><abbr>suoru</abbr><ex>m</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="4"/>et colllegarum
                    <lb n="5"/><persName type="divine" key="nymphaAugusta"><name>Nymphis</name> <name><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustis</ex></expan></name></persName>
                    <lb n="6"/>votum posuit
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text from EDR; comparison with photograph.</note></app>
                    <app loc="3"><note>EDR reads an "M" at the end of line 3, which is not visible from the photograph. I have chosen to render it here as an abbreviation suoru(m) but it is possible that this was written in subscript in the middle of the line, as in the form of the end of the word in the following line.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Titus Flavius Optatus, for the safety of himself, his family and the college of Nympha Augusta. He fulfilled this vow.</p>
            </div>
